abstract: PHILADELPHIA, Jan. 5 (AP) -- The Philadelphia 76ers turned back a second-half Detroit rally and posted a 126-119 victory over the Pistons today in a National Basketball Association game.

abstract: After having won nine straight games for the first time in more than 22 years, the New York Knickerbockers will attempt to set a club record for consecutive victories tonight when they oppose the Detroit Pistons in a National Basketball Association game at Madison Square Garden.

abstract: YONKERS, Jan. 3 -- The return of horse racing of the harness variety, was an unqualified success at the Yonkers Raceway tonight. In 33-degree weather a crowd of 25,170 turned out for the opening of the 52-night meeting.
